1
00:00:05,166 --> 00:00:05,969
Our troupe

2
00:00:06,412 --> 00:00:08,733
Will never let our spark
fade again.

3
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:10,000
Honestly,

4
00:00:10,399 --> 00:00:12,392
I think what happened between you and Guy

5
00:00:12,392 --> 00:00:15,000
has been weighing on your heart for a long time.

6
00:00:15,766 --> 00:00:16,566
Alright then.

7
00:00:17,400 --> 00:00:18,300
Let’s be together.

8
00:00:18,933 --> 00:00:19,733
P'Ploy.

9
00:00:20,966 --> 00:00:23,796
People at the market are gossiping right now.

10
00:00:24,062 --> 00:00:25,196
They’re saying that P'Ploy

11
00:00:25,994 --> 00:00:27,065
is pregnant.

12
00:00:27,266 --> 00:00:29,029
Those leaked off-screen photos of you two

13
00:00:29,029 --> 00:00:30,000
are way too sweet.

14
00:00:30,266 --> 00:00:32,031
Some people only like imaginary couples,

15
00:00:32,430 --> 00:00:33,399
not real ones.

16
00:00:38,831 --> 00:00:45,716
Ploy Ying Pregnant with Phet Thae’s Child.

17
00:00:50,666 --> 00:00:53,920
Today, everyone is waiting to hear
the answer from you, Phet Thae.

18
00:00:53,920 --> 00:00:58,448
About the rumor that Ploy Ying
of the Petchprakai Troupe is pregnant.

19
00:00:58,448 --> 00:01:02,500
After she collapsed on stage,
is it true?

20
00:01:18,600 --> 00:01:19,733
That’s not true.

21
00:01:20,900 --> 00:01:22,522
That day Ploy Ying fainted

22
00:01:23,098 --> 00:01:25,404
because she hadn’t gotten enough rest from rehearsing so hard.

23
00:01:25,759 --> 00:01:28,666
Nothing happened between us
like the rumors say.

24
00:01:28,933 --> 00:01:32,202
So you’re confirming
there’s no intimate relationship

25
00:01:32,202 --> 00:01:33,661
beyond work?

26
00:01:34,149 --> 00:01:36,900
But people saw the two of you
going to the hospital together.

27
00:01:36,900 --> 00:01:38,200
And you seemed very close.

28
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:39,622
Yes.

29
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:41,360
We went to the hospital together

30
00:01:41,981 --> 00:01:43,666
because I was worried about her.

31
00:01:48,933 --> 00:01:50,675
And if you want to say we’re close,

32
00:01:51,074 --> 00:01:52,466
I won’t deny it.

33
00:01:52,733 --> 00:01:53,233
Mm.

34
00:01:53,588 --> 00:01:55,590
So are you saying

35
00:01:55,945 --> 00:01:58,211
that you’re dating?

36
00:02:02,933 --> 00:02:03,944
Yes.

37
00:02:04,742 --> 00:02:05,989
Ploy Ying and I

38
00:02:06,698 --> 00:02:07,877
are really together.

39
00:02:12,466 --> 00:02:14,912
Saying it this openly means

40
00:02:14,912 --> 00:02:17,100
you’re not afraid it’ll affect the troupe’s image?

41
00:02:17,666 --> 00:02:19,972
If it does, then I’ll accept it.

42
00:02:20,548 --> 00:02:21,392
Because

43
00:02:22,013 --> 00:02:23,470
I don’t want there to be any misunderstanding.

44
00:02:24,046 --> 00:02:26,110
I care about the reputation of the person I love.

45
00:02:32,333 --> 00:02:35,196
I won’t let anyone hurt her with rumors

46
00:02:35,196 --> 00:02:36,966
or words ever again.

47
00:02:51,666 --> 00:02:53,261
And now that everyone knows,

48
00:02:53,837 --> 00:02:55,243
I’ll say it right here.

49
00:02:56,484 --> 00:02:58,265
I love Ploy Ying.

50
00:02:59,200 --> 00:03:01,466
And from today onward, I’ll stand by her side

51
00:03:02,733 --> 00:03:04,533
like a man should.

52
00:03:06,100 --> 00:03:07,600
That sounds so heartfelt.

53
00:03:08,266 --> 00:03:10,700
And this is the answer straight from Phet Thae’s heart

54
00:03:10,766 --> 00:03:12,066
that everyone has been waiting for.

55
00:03:12,466 --> 00:03:13,966
Thank you very much for today.

56
00:03:19,933 --> 00:03:20,933
That was amazing.

57
00:03:21,866 --> 00:03:23,100
So damn manly.

58
00:03:33,533 --> 00:03:34,766
You did great today.

59
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:36,800
Thank you.

60
00:03:38,333 --> 00:03:40,605
Hey, the two of us did really well today.

61
00:03:40,871 --> 00:03:42,100
The audience cracked up laughing.

62
00:03:42,400 --> 00:03:45,366
“Cracked up” means laughing, right?
Not the studio literally exploding?

63
00:03:45,533 --> 00:03:46,333
No way.

64
00:03:46,466 --> 00:03:47,671
If the studio really exploded,

65
00:03:47,981 --> 00:03:49,700
we’d have to bring the Petchprakai Troupe over to put it out.

66
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:50,444
But hey,

67
00:03:50,444 --> 00:03:52,739
Phet Thae’s filming
in the next studio over.

68
00:03:52,739 --> 00:03:54,466
I heard he’s about to announce something too.

69
00:03:58,766 --> 00:04:00,065
We used to be part of

70
00:04:00,464 --> 00:04:02,100
the Petchprakai Likay Troupe too, right?

71
00:04:02,500 --> 00:04:03,300
I remember.

72
00:04:04,866 --> 00:04:06,266
Alright then, I’ll get going first.

73
00:04:06,600 --> 00:04:07,485
Okay.

74
00:04:07,485 --> 00:04:07,985
Alright.

75
00:04:13,766 --> 00:04:15,900
Looks like this news is really blowing up.

76
00:04:16,966 --> 00:04:18,533
Can your brother handle it?

77
00:04:22,866 --> 00:04:24,191
If it’s P'Phet Thae,

78
00:04:25,343 --> 00:04:26,310
he won’t run away.

79
00:05:57,966 --> 00:05:59,562
And now that everyone knows,

80
00:06:00,266 --> 00:06:01,534
I’ll say it right here.

81
00:06:02,066 --> 00:06:03,402
I love Ploy Ying.

82
00:06:03,845 --> 00:06:06,309
And from today onward, I’ll stand by her side

83
00:06:06,708 --> 00:06:08,062
like a man should.

84
00:06:08,816 --> 00:06:09,797
Phet Thae and Ploy Ying are perfect together,
both on-screen and off-screen.

85
00:06:09,797 --> 00:06:11,167
Exactly. That’s absolutely right.
Protecting the one you love.

86
00:06:11,168 --> 00:06:12,148
Admire this couple. They’re both so adorable.

87
00:06:12,148 --> 00:06:13,762
Nothing but this kind of news lately,

88
00:06:13,763 --> 00:06:15,229
but the shows just aren’t fun anymore.

89
00:06:15,230 --> 00:06:17,230
Why focus on pushing the ship, not the actual performance.

90
00:06:17,231 --> 00:06:19,037
Other troupes don’t have scandals,
yet their Likay performances are way better.

91
00:06:19,037 --> 00:06:22,356
Other troupes have already gone so much further.

92
00:06:32,466 --> 00:06:33,266
Ploy.

93
00:06:34,366 --> 00:06:35,166
Yeah?

94
00:06:39,066 --> 00:06:39,839
I think

95
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:41,385
if we keep performing the same way,

96
00:06:42,581 --> 00:06:44,239
people will stop watching us soon.

97
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:47,566
Not because they don’t love us,

98
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:50,066
but because we’re still

99
00:06:50,900 --> 00:06:52,900
telling them the same stories every day.

100
00:06:54,800 --> 00:06:55,830
You mean

101
00:06:56,229 --> 00:06:57,323
change our style?

102
00:07:04,966 --> 00:07:05,910
If so,

103
00:07:06,974 --> 00:07:08,707
we need to start with stories

104
00:07:09,372 --> 00:07:11,188
that truly come from us.

105
00:07:12,733 --> 00:07:14,625
Maybe from the troupe’s life,

106
00:07:15,201 --> 00:07:16,274
from our dreams,

107
00:07:16,673 --> 00:07:18,615
or from things we once lost.

108
00:07:19,369 --> 00:07:22,272
Then weave them into Likay
in the Petchprakai style.

109
00:07:23,021 --> 00:07:24,156
So people can see

110
00:07:24,732 --> 00:07:27,639
that Likay can still tell today’s stories.

111
00:07:33,133 --> 00:07:34,310
The stories of today

112
00:07:35,329 --> 00:07:37,157
might sound ordinary,

113
00:07:38,176 --> 00:07:39,275
but I think

114
00:07:40,738 --> 00:07:42,355
they could become our legend.

115
00:07:45,766 --> 00:07:46,855
Then—

116
00:07:47,077 --> 00:07:48,146
tonight,

117
00:07:48,811 --> 00:07:50,000
shall we begin, P'Phet?

118
00:08:06,300 --> 00:08:07,905
Write down whatever comes to mind, Ploy.

119
00:08:07,905 --> 00:08:08,466
Okay.

120
00:08:25,466 --> 00:08:26,266
Mm.

121
00:08:26,700 --> 00:08:27,766
How about this word?

122
00:08:28,266 --> 00:08:29,208
“Spark of Love.”

123
00:08:29,518 --> 00:08:30,576
I wrote it down.

124
00:08:31,100 --> 00:08:31,900
This one.

125
00:08:33,543 --> 00:08:36,917
♪ Since the moment I laid eyes upon you ♪

126
00:08:49,400 --> 00:08:49,952
♪ Your skin ♪

127
00:08:50,351 --> 00:08:51,699
♪ Fair and golden ♪

128
00:08:52,866 --> 00:08:54,133
♪ Your fair golden skin ♪

129
00:09:02,766 --> 00:09:03,600
♪ Shines radiant ♪

130
00:09:05,482 --> 00:09:06,108
♪ Like ♪

131
00:09:06,569 --> 00:09:08,569
♪ Like pure gold ♪

132
00:09:09,590 --> 00:09:10,349
♪ So graceful and fair ♪

133
00:09:12,500 --> 00:09:14,327
When you’re the Likay hero on stage,

134
00:09:15,258 --> 00:09:16,855
you never let yourself get tired.

135
00:09:18,966 --> 00:09:20,602
But the moment you got a girlfriend,

136
00:09:22,109 --> 00:09:23,403
why are you writing love scenes

137
00:09:24,157 --> 00:09:25,755
until you exhaust yourself like this?

138
00:09:28,666 --> 00:09:30,740
I just want the script to come out as perfect as possible.

139
00:09:31,804 --> 00:09:33,354
So Ploy won’t have to work too hard.

140
00:09:45,866 --> 00:09:46,990
But what if

141
00:09:48,231 --> 00:09:50,575
I want to hear it from you right now,

142
00:09:53,456 --> 00:09:55,110
not from the script?

143
00:10:13,100 --> 00:10:13,900
Ploy…

144
00:10:18,366 --> 00:10:19,166
I…

145
00:10:33,665 --> 00:10:34,766
I…

146
00:10:35,032 --> 00:10:36,166
P'Phet! P'Ploy!

147
00:10:36,866 --> 00:10:38,100
Something huge happened!

148
00:10:42,566 --> 00:10:43,066
You—

149
00:10:43,066 --> 00:10:43,766
Pleng!

150
00:10:44,700 --> 00:10:45,766
You’re doing this again?

151
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:47,366
You came in without knocking?

152
00:10:47,533 --> 00:10:48,266
Sorry.

153
00:10:48,266 --> 00:10:49,733
I didn’t mean to peek.

154
00:10:50,566 --> 00:10:52,000
I wasn’t trying to spy on you, but—

155
00:10:52,933 --> 00:10:55,533
this really is serious.

156
00:11:02,533 --> 00:11:03,766
What is it?

157
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:26,422
This “huge thing”—

158
00:11:26,777 --> 00:11:28,299
does it involve the troupe?

159
00:11:28,966 --> 00:11:30,264
Not at all.

160
00:11:30,486 --> 00:11:32,767
The troupe’s perfectly fine.

161
00:11:35,766 --> 00:11:36,733
Then is it about money?

162
00:11:36,966 --> 00:11:38,166
Nope, not that either.

163
00:11:38,609 --> 00:11:40,603
Every single baht is still there.

164
00:11:40,603 --> 00:11:42,100
No scammers drained it away.

165
00:11:42,266 --> 00:11:42,780
Ugh.

166
00:11:43,268 --> 00:11:45,016
Then what the hell is this about, Pleng?

167
00:11:45,282 --> 00:11:46,711
Spit it out already.

168
00:11:48,300 --> 00:11:49,100
Well…

169
00:12:03,733 --> 00:12:04,754
Here.

170
00:12:07,502 --> 00:12:08,547
Got it.

171
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:10,786
Thank you.

172
00:12:10,786 --> 00:12:14,034
Can I get your Line?
A handsome guy like you can’t say no.

173
00:12:27,200 --> 00:12:28,283
Nope.

174
00:12:28,505 --> 00:12:29,938
He’s courting me right now.

175
00:12:30,931 --> 00:12:32,047
Please don’t interfere.

176
00:12:32,313 --> 00:12:34,340
Or you might not find your way home.

177
00:12:35,614 --> 00:12:36,506
Thank you.

178
00:12:43,166 --> 00:12:44,428
Lynchee,

179
00:12:45,004 --> 00:12:47,918
if you’re going to flirt with me this aggressively,

180
00:12:48,184 --> 00:12:49,068
please

181
00:12:49,822 --> 00:12:50,894
take a number and line up.

182
00:12:51,515 --> 00:12:52,731
These days,

183
00:12:53,041 --> 00:12:55,744
I’m kinda hot right now.

184
00:12:56,099 --> 00:12:57,225
Just a little.

185
00:12:57,600 --> 00:12:58,154
Go ahead.

186
00:13:00,200 --> 00:13:01,000
Sigh…

187
00:13:02,400 --> 00:13:03,166
Here.

188
00:13:03,166 --> 00:13:05,366
I’ll give you twenty points out of a hundred for today.

189
00:13:05,700 --> 00:13:06,966
For that hotness earlier.

190
00:13:07,566 --> 00:13:08,733
If you don’t flop later,

191
00:13:08,766 --> 00:13:09,566
I’ll raise your score.

192
00:13:13,533 --> 00:13:14,700
Now I’m curious.

193
00:13:15,365 --> 00:13:15,927
About whether

194
00:13:16,237 --> 00:13:18,983
this hotness upgrade thing

195
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:22,772
works like ranking up in a game.

196
00:13:23,260 --> 00:13:25,951
Because I’m aiming for Diamond rank.

197
00:13:26,986 --> 00:13:28,581
Nothing too crazy.

198
00:13:30,533 --> 00:13:31,822
Better keep grinding first.

199
00:13:32,354 --> 00:13:33,136
Because today,

200
00:13:33,757 --> 00:13:36,643
I’m taking you to the Headman-level dungeon.

201
00:13:40,566 --> 00:13:41,366
Huh?

202
00:13:48,466 --> 00:13:49,566
P'Phet, P'Ploy—

203
00:13:50,733 --> 00:13:53,066
You understand how nervous I am, right?

204
00:13:54,333 --> 00:13:56,066
I’m about to meet her father.

205
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:58,000
I seriously don’t know how to deal with adults.

206
00:13:59,933 --> 00:14:01,066
I really don’t.

207
00:14:02,966 --> 00:14:03,826
Don’t tell me—

208
00:14:04,447 --> 00:14:06,266
you got his daughter—

209
00:14:06,266 --> 00:14:07,972
No! No, not like that!

210
00:14:07,972 --> 00:14:09,081
Not like that, stop imagining things.

211
00:14:09,391 --> 00:14:12,000
These days, even holding hands is hard enough.

212
00:14:12,533 --> 00:14:13,333
And as for—

213
00:14:13,500 --> 00:14:14,329
it’s not like that!

214
00:14:15,171 --> 00:14:16,809
Stop teasing him.

215
00:14:21,133 --> 00:14:22,900
Hello, P'Phet and P'Ploy.

216
00:14:23,400 --> 00:14:24,200
Hello.

217
00:14:24,666 --> 00:14:25,866
Hi there.

218
00:14:27,166 --> 00:14:28,966
Hello, Pleng Chai.

219
00:14:30,866 --> 00:14:32,766
Today I’m taking Pleng to meet my dad.

220
00:14:34,166 --> 00:14:36,066
If he’s going to court someone’s daughter,

221
00:14:36,466 --> 00:14:37,725
he has to be brave enough to face the parents.

222
00:14:37,947 --> 00:14:38,522
Right?

223
00:14:40,766 --> 00:14:41,413
Hey.

224
00:14:43,097 --> 00:14:44,754
You’ve come this far already.

225
00:14:46,700 --> 00:14:47,733
Just be sincere.

226
00:14:48,300 --> 00:14:50,710
Let’s hope Headman Mai isn’t too sincere

227
00:14:51,066 --> 00:14:54,066
and shoots you right between the eyes.

228
00:14:54,500 --> 00:14:56,600
One shot, dead.
Haven’t you seen it in movies?

229
00:14:56,800 --> 00:14:57,533
What are you saying?

230
00:14:57,533 --> 00:14:58,733
If Dad really shoots him,

231
00:14:59,300 --> 00:15:01,700
I’ll drag his corpse back to the troupe myself.

232
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:02,800
Lynchee…

233
00:15:03,800 --> 00:15:04,600
Scared?

234
00:15:04,866 --> 00:15:05,733
I’m kidding.

235
00:15:06,600 --> 00:15:08,078
If we’re going to meet adults,

236
00:15:08,699 --> 00:15:09,841
this big sister right here

237
00:15:10,240 --> 00:15:11,703
will be the adult on our side.

238
00:15:12,545 --> 00:15:13,383
Mm, I’ll go too.

239
00:15:13,959 --> 00:15:16,207
I want to thank Uncle Headman as well.

240
00:15:16,428 --> 00:15:17,988
For always helping the troupe.

241
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:22,281
The atmosphere right now

242
00:15:22,503 --> 00:15:25,188
feels like we’re heading for a marriage proposal.

243
00:15:29,166 --> 00:15:29,666
Yeah.

244
00:15:31,350 --> 00:15:32,822
If I was brave enough to ask,

245
00:15:33,487 --> 00:15:34,566
then you'll be brave enough to accept too.

246
00:15:36,500 --> 00:15:37,433
Too soon!

247
00:15:38,054 --> 00:15:39,311
Earn a full score first.

248
00:15:44,666 --> 00:15:47,333
Then let’s go see my daddy.

249
00:15:48,066 --> 00:15:48,866
Ready?

250
00:15:48,936 --> 00:15:49,533
We’re going now?

251
00:15:49,533 --> 00:15:50,091
Of course.

252
00:15:50,091 --> 00:15:50,844
Let’s go.

253
00:15:50,844 --> 00:15:51,366
Go.

254
00:15:51,366 --> 00:15:52,166
Move it.

255
00:16:01,100 --> 00:16:01,900
Hello.

256
00:16:02,533 --> 00:16:03,452
Is this him?

257
00:16:04,383 --> 00:16:05,445
The one courting my daughter?

258
00:16:06,597 --> 00:16:07,333
Yes, sir.

259
00:16:08,666 --> 00:16:09,766
I’m serious about her.

260
00:16:12,466 --> 00:16:13,466
How serious?

261
00:16:17,100 --> 00:16:18,086
I study hard.

262
00:16:18,707 --> 00:16:20,000
I work honestly.

263
00:16:20,665 --> 00:16:23,278
And I swear to you, Uncle Headman,

264
00:16:23,721 --> 00:16:25,949
that I’ll take the best care of Lynchee.

265
00:16:27,323 --> 00:16:28,131
If…

266
00:16:28,885 --> 00:16:29,760
you don’t…

267
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:31,352
shoot me first.

268
00:16:32,771 --> 00:16:33,708
Uncle,

269
00:16:34,196 --> 00:16:36,763
Pleng has really changed
a lot lately.

270
00:16:37,206 --> 00:16:39,517
Back then, whenever he performed,

271
00:16:39,517 --> 00:16:42,072
he worried people wouldn’t laugh. But now,

272
00:16:42,648 --> 00:16:44,976
the only thing he fears is not being accepted by you.

273
00:16:46,400 --> 00:16:47,230
Exactly.

274
00:16:47,230 --> 00:16:50,439
Pleng’s become a good kid who’s serious about studying.

275
00:16:50,794 --> 00:16:52,316
He’s not reckless like before anymore.

276
00:16:52,893 --> 00:16:56,867
And when it comes to Lynchee,
he’s just as serious as he is about school.

277
00:17:02,933 --> 00:17:04,466
And if I tell you to break up?

278
00:17:05,333 --> 00:17:06,133
What would you do?

279
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:24,466
I won’t break up with her, Uncle Headman.

280
00:17:25,933 --> 00:17:28,300
I might seem playful,

281
00:17:29,366 --> 00:17:31,025
but when it comes to this,

282
00:17:31,823 --> 00:17:33,175
I’m completely serious.

283
00:17:33,485 --> 00:17:36,416
Even when I stream games, I take it seriously.

284
00:17:36,815 --> 00:17:39,437
So when it’s about someone I love,

285
00:17:40,000 --> 00:17:41,564
I’m even more serious than that.

286
00:17:43,337 --> 00:17:44,581
If I love someone,

287
00:17:45,157 --> 00:17:48,177
I’ll push through every quest and never give up.

288
00:17:49,418 --> 00:17:53,577
But if I do my absolute best

289
00:17:53,932 --> 00:17:56,855
and one day Lynchee doesn’t wait for me anymore,

290
00:18:01,600 --> 00:18:04,468
I’ll accept it.

291
00:18:04,689 --> 00:18:08,339
Because I know love can’t be forced.

292
00:18:08,339 --> 00:18:10,554
Unlike game characters I can control.

293
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:38,982
You’re a good person.

294
00:18:39,292 --> 00:18:40,340
You have a future ahead of you.

295
00:18:41,005 --> 00:18:42,800
I can trust my daughter with you.

296
00:18:46,200 --> 00:18:48,900
You can trust me, Uncle Headman.

297
00:18:49,900 --> 00:18:51,090
Oh, come on, Dad.

298
00:18:51,489 --> 00:18:53,866
This is so tense I can barely breathe.

299
00:18:53,866 --> 00:18:55,243
Why are you pretending to be strict?

300
00:18:55,509 --> 00:18:58,255
You were excited to meet
Pleng today too, weren’t you?

301
00:19:00,333 --> 00:19:01,607
I’m just soft-hearted.

302
00:19:02,139 --> 00:19:04,620
When I see kids brave enough to speak and act like this,

303
00:19:05,462 --> 00:19:06,910
I can’t help feeling proud.

304
00:19:08,611 --> 00:19:09,813
Daddy.

305
00:19:11,500 --> 00:19:12,650
Then today,

306
00:19:13,005 --> 00:19:16,455
Lynchee’s adding twenty more points, making it

307
00:19:19,333 --> 00:19:21,400
officially ready-to-date status.

308
00:19:22,566 --> 00:19:24,300
Future son-in-law.

309
00:19:27,333 --> 00:19:28,466
Seventy points already?

310
00:19:30,166 --> 00:19:32,733
That levels up even faster than
the games I play.

311
00:19:33,733 --> 00:19:34,533
Absolutely.

312
00:19:38,100 --> 00:19:39,266
Yes, Lynchee.

313
00:19:39,466 --> 00:19:40,766
I’m ready to go on a date with you.

314
00:19:41,500 --> 00:19:43,733
Then how about we go on a date tomorrow?

315
00:19:44,533 --> 00:19:47,100
Something casual, no need to dress up too much.

316
00:19:47,966 --> 00:19:50,814
Simple and easy. I’ll take you to our regular spot.

317
00:19:50,814 --> 00:19:52,594
It’s an amazing place. A fried banana shop.

318
00:19:52,860 --> 00:19:53,947
My regular place.

319
00:19:54,302 --> 00:19:55,185
Mark my words,

320
00:19:55,185 --> 00:19:58,577
it's better than every rare item
I’ve ever gotten in a game.

321
00:19:59,133 --> 00:19:59,866
It’s so good.

322
00:19:59,866 --> 00:20:02,500
Wow, fried bananas. So romantic.

323
00:20:02,900 --> 00:20:04,432
Of course.

324
00:20:04,432 --> 00:20:06,463
Every relationship has to start with fried food.

325
00:20:06,463 --> 00:20:07,333
And after that,

326
00:20:07,933 --> 00:20:09,533
we’ll continue with dessert.

327
00:20:10,133 --> 00:20:10,845
Oh my.

328
00:20:11,566 --> 00:20:12,500
What are you saying?

329
00:20:13,066 --> 00:20:13,866
Uh—

330
00:20:14,200 --> 00:20:16,346
Uncle Headman, no! That’s not what I meant.

331
00:20:16,612 --> 00:20:19,320
By dessert, I meant actual dessert.

332
00:20:19,320 --> 00:20:21,024
No, not like that at all.

333
00:20:21,024 --> 00:20:24,613
Like shaved ice or sweet dumplings or something.

334
00:20:24,613 --> 00:20:26,266
Not… not like that.

335
00:20:28,056 --> 00:20:28,859
Help.

336
00:20:30,001 --> 00:20:30,982
You keep getting off track.

337
00:20:31,737 --> 00:20:32,895
Daddy.

338
00:20:33,577 --> 00:20:35,577
I really didn’t mean it like that.

339
00:20:47,333 --> 00:20:50,264
Those leaked off-screen photos of
you two are way too sweet.

340
00:20:51,727 --> 00:20:52,677
From now on,

341
00:20:53,652 --> 00:20:55,722
keep the sweetness only for public appearances.

342
00:20:56,165 --> 00:20:57,120
Understand?

343
00:20:57,785 --> 00:21:00,610
Some people only like imaginary couples, not real ones.

344
00:21:08,733 --> 00:21:09,533
You.

345
00:21:10,366 --> 00:21:11,166
Hm.

346
00:21:12,100 --> 00:21:13,781
We’ll let time prove it.

347
00:21:14,446 --> 00:21:16,045
Let people come to accept the two of us.

348
00:21:19,766 --> 00:21:20,631
Thank you

349
00:21:21,872 --> 00:21:23,644
for always staying by my side.

350
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:48,500
It’s time to rehearse the script.

351
00:21:48,766 --> 00:21:49,566
What script now?

352
00:21:55,900 --> 00:21:56,893
NC scenes.

353
00:21:57,912 --> 00:21:59,067
Like… special ones.

354
00:22:55,933 --> 00:22:58,317
People on social media are talking a lot right now.

355
00:22:58,317 --> 00:23:00,564
They’re saying the Petchprakai Troupe might have internal problems,
[Entertainment Drama]

356
00:23:00,564 --> 00:23:03,581
especially between
Phet Thae and Tor Prakai.

357
00:23:03,581 --> 00:23:05,617
Because ever since the troupe became famous again,

358
00:23:05,617 --> 00:23:08,272
the two of them haven’t appeared together at events anymore.

359
00:23:08,272 --> 00:23:10,066
Is this rumor true?

360
00:23:10,700 --> 00:23:12,284
Rumors are just rumors.

361
00:23:12,993 --> 00:23:14,723
Just because people can’t see something

362
00:23:15,122 --> 00:23:16,999
doesn’t mean it isn’t real.

363
00:23:17,974 --> 00:23:20,299
I don’t think this is drama at all.

364
00:23:20,742 --> 00:23:22,954
It’s simply a time when everyone in the troupe

365
00:23:22,954 --> 00:23:25,126
is searching for something new together.

366
00:23:25,126 --> 00:23:27,179
Because every spark, no matter who it comes from,

367
00:23:27,179 --> 00:23:28,888
will always shine toward one another’s hearts.

368
00:23:30,600 --> 00:23:31,401
Thank you.

369
00:23:32,022 --> 00:23:33,618
I hope everyone will keep watching.

370
00:23:34,283 --> 00:23:35,880
This time, it’s not just about Likay.

371
00:23:36,545 --> 00:23:38,389
It’s about the true hearts

372
00:23:38,389 --> 00:23:39,591
of all of us.

373
00:23:40,433 --> 00:23:41,347
Okay then.

374
00:23:41,347 --> 00:23:43,943
Can I get a photo with you two?

375
00:23:48,159 --> 00:23:49,577
#TorPrakaiCan’tWaitToSeeYourNextWork

376
00:23:49,578 --> 00:23:51,044
This couple has great chemistry.

377
00:23:51,045 --> 00:23:55,617
#NineGuyForever

378
00:23:56,866 --> 00:23:57,666
See?

379
00:23:58,000 --> 00:24:00,166
Your little brother never really ran away from you.

380
00:24:03,266 --> 00:24:06,266
I think he’s seriously becoming famous now.

381
00:24:06,566 --> 00:24:07,366
Look at this.

382
00:24:07,600 --> 00:24:09,566
The hashtag “Tor Prakai” is all over the feed.

383
00:24:11,333 --> 00:24:12,261
Honestly,

384
00:24:13,015 --> 00:24:14,937
even though Guy is in Bangkok,

385
00:24:15,336 --> 00:24:17,755
the way he talks about the troupe—

386
00:24:18,464 --> 00:24:19,599
you already know

387
00:24:20,663 --> 00:24:21,973
the heart of Petchprakai

388
00:24:22,638 --> 00:24:23,821
is still here.

389
00:24:26,171 --> 00:24:27,395
Sometimes,

390
00:24:27,838 --> 00:24:30,627
you have to let
the younger generation grow.

391
00:24:31,336 --> 00:24:32,782
And not just Guy,

392
00:24:33,048 --> 00:24:34,521
but you too.

393
00:24:36,383 --> 00:24:37,600
You sound like a mother.

394
00:24:38,666 --> 00:24:39,466
Right?

395
00:24:40,700 --> 00:24:41,500
Yeah.

396
00:24:41,933 --> 00:24:44,533
Then should we go see Guy now?

397
00:24:45,066 --> 00:24:47,266
That way it’ll end up going viral.

398
00:24:47,900 --> 00:24:50,066
Like “big brother brings little brother home” or something.

399
00:24:50,300 --> 00:24:51,100
How about it?

400
00:24:52,100 --> 00:24:52,917
Sounds good.

401
00:24:54,069 --> 00:24:56,044
I think it’s finally time for us to talk.

402
00:24:56,975 --> 00:24:58,828
This time, I’ll lead the way.

403
00:24:59,183 --> 00:25:00,466
I’ll take you to him myself.

404
00:25:00,466 --> 00:25:02,346
You sure you remember the way?

405
00:25:02,346 --> 00:25:05,902
Last time you went shopping,
Lynchee still had to escort you back to the hotel.

406
00:25:05,902 --> 00:25:06,900
Didn’t she?

407
00:25:07,133 --> 00:25:08,533
No, that time—

408
00:25:09,100 --> 00:25:09,966
I wasn’t lost.

409
00:25:10,133 --> 00:25:11,533
Listen to me, I know the way now.

410
00:25:11,700 --> 00:25:12,500
Just keep going straight.

411
00:25:12,766 --> 00:25:13,766
Then this time,

412
00:25:13,933 --> 00:25:15,766
let’s at least make it back before sunset.

413
00:25:16,533 --> 00:25:17,333
Deal.

414
00:25:17,733 --> 00:25:19,500
Then let’s get ready to head out.

415
00:25:19,866 --> 00:25:21,533
Just don’t get me lost this time.

416
00:25:21,666 --> 00:25:22,566
No way I’ll get lost.

417
00:25:23,933 --> 00:25:24,797
Can you trust me or not?

418
00:25:24,797 --> 00:25:25,297
Hey.

419
00:25:25,466 --> 00:25:26,366
You really don’t trust me, huh?

420
00:25:43,966 --> 00:25:45,051
Today, I have to say it.

421
00:25:45,539 --> 00:25:47,654
How much I love him.

422
00:25:55,300 --> 00:25:56,100
Who are you?

423
00:26:00,733 --> 00:26:02,133
Do you know whose house this is?

424
00:26:02,533 --> 00:26:03,700
You’ve stayed here far too long.

425
00:26:03,933 --> 00:26:05,466
Today, I’m coming back to live here.

426
00:26:12,133 --> 00:26:12,914
You—

427
00:26:13,668 --> 00:26:14,932
You lied to me.

428
00:26:18,766 --> 00:26:19,666
What’s going on?

429
00:26:25,666 --> 00:26:26,180
Fine.

430
00:26:26,579 --> 00:26:27,543
I’ll leave myself.

431
00:26:28,100 --> 00:26:29,262
Hey, wait, Guy!

432
00:26:30,902 --> 00:26:32,776
Can you stop causing problems for once?

433
00:26:43,066 --> 00:26:43,652
Guy—

434
00:26:43,652 --> 00:26:44,200
(Pleng Chai) Hey!
(Lynchee) Hey!

435
00:26:44,600 --> 00:26:45,400
What happened?

436
00:26:46,366 --> 00:26:47,400
Why is this happening?

437
00:26:53,766 --> 00:26:55,400
Did we come too late?

438
00:27:09,533 --> 00:27:10,320
Uh…

439
00:27:11,694 --> 00:27:13,365
Now that everyone’s here,

440
00:27:13,631 --> 00:27:15,166
it actually feels kinda warm.

441
00:27:17,766 --> 00:27:18,448
Guy.

442
00:27:20,310 --> 00:27:22,123
If you’re not ready to talk right now, that’s okay.

443
00:27:22,655 --> 00:27:24,316
But come home first.

444
00:27:24,759 --> 00:27:25,854
Everyone’s worried.

445
00:27:27,848 --> 00:27:28,872
Wait a second.

446
00:27:29,734 --> 00:27:31,729
It’s not what everyone thinks at all.

447
00:27:39,533 --> 00:27:40,177
I think

448
00:27:40,487 --> 00:27:41,497
at this point,

449
00:27:42,029 --> 00:27:43,754
the lead couple is definitely fighting.

450
00:28:06,333 --> 00:28:07,140
Can you answer me?

451
00:28:07,761 --> 00:28:08,645
What exactly happened?

452
00:28:10,000 --> 00:28:10,911
Everyone—

453
00:28:11,443 --> 00:28:14,244
Can’t you see how much
we look alike?

454
00:28:35,066 --> 00:28:36,933
This is my real younger brother.

455
00:28:38,700 --> 00:28:39,533
His name is Ten.

456
00:28:39,534 --> 00:28:41,445
Whoa!

457
00:28:43,666 --> 00:28:45,904
I’m sorry for making everyone misunderstand.

458
00:28:45,904 --> 00:28:48,210
Nine likes teasing me,

459
00:28:48,210 --> 00:28:49,535
so I decided to mess with him first.

460
00:28:49,535 --> 00:28:51,956
And the reason none of you
have seen me before is because

461
00:28:52,577 --> 00:28:53,939
I told him not to post me on social media.

462
00:28:53,939 --> 00:28:55,412
I didn’t want things getting messy.

463
00:29:05,955 --> 00:29:07,166
But we really do look alike, huh?

464
00:29:35,066 --> 00:29:35,866
Yeah.

465
00:29:37,666 --> 00:29:38,466
Sorry.

466
00:29:39,366 --> 00:29:40,500
We misunderstood.

467
00:29:42,300 --> 00:29:43,100
Hey.

468
00:29:43,366 --> 00:29:44,866
Trust me, Guy.

469
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:45,900
In this industry,

470
00:29:46,100 --> 00:29:47,666
there are still plenty of good people.

471
00:29:49,200 --> 00:29:50,933
We just have to trust each other.

472
00:29:58,600 --> 00:29:59,100
Okay.

473
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:01,002
I trust you.

474
00:30:09,933 --> 00:30:12,133
Now it’s our turn, Guy.

475
00:30:13,933 --> 00:30:14,733
Huh?

476
00:30:17,733 --> 00:30:19,700
Is P'Phet about to kiss Tor Prakai on the cheek?

477
00:30:20,333 --> 00:30:21,133
I’m not joking.

478
00:30:24,500 --> 00:30:25,041
Oops.

479
00:30:25,351 --> 00:30:26,210
I need to pee.

480
00:30:27,200 --> 00:30:28,066
I’m going to the bathroom.

481
00:30:28,500 --> 00:30:29,700
Oh, I’ll go too.

482
00:30:32,333 --> 00:30:34,700
Well, if there’s nothing else, I’ll head to bed.

483
00:30:35,100 --> 00:30:36,133
Oh, sure.

484
00:30:36,700 --> 00:30:37,500
Upstairs.

485
00:30:37,566 --> 00:30:38,366
Go ahead… please.

486
00:30:38,966 --> 00:30:40,366
Good night.

487
00:30:40,533 --> 00:30:41,200
Sweet dreams.

488
00:30:41,200 --> 00:30:42,000
Hurry upstairs now.

489
00:30:44,100 --> 00:30:44,929
Hey, Nine.

490
00:30:45,328 --> 00:30:46,566
Where’s the kitchen?

491
00:30:47,066 --> 00:30:47,866
This way.

492
00:30:47,900 --> 00:30:49,566
Oh… excuse me then.

493
00:31:09,400 --> 00:31:10,200
Guy.

494
00:31:12,733 --> 00:31:14,400
Looking at you today,

495
00:31:15,500 --> 00:31:17,800
I’ve never seen you
this happy before.

496
00:31:28,266 --> 00:31:29,578
So many times,

497
00:31:30,000 --> 00:31:31,443
I wanted to say it,

498
00:31:31,797 --> 00:31:32,949
but I never could.

499
00:31:37,737 --> 00:31:38,800
P'Phet…

500
00:31:42,733 --> 00:31:43,843
I want to—

501
00:31:43,843 --> 00:31:44,798
Hey, Guy.

502
00:31:45,064 --> 00:31:46,143
Perfect timing.

503
00:31:46,143 --> 00:31:49,148
Go wash the curtains for me.

504
00:31:49,148 --> 00:31:51,450
And the Likay costumes we’ll be wearing too.

505
00:31:51,450 --> 00:31:52,810
Wash all of them.

506
00:31:53,310 --> 00:31:53,810
Well—

507
00:31:54,866 --> 00:31:57,381
We don’t know when work will come in again,
but one thing’s certain—

508
00:31:57,381 --> 00:31:59,318
our troupe has to be ready.

509
00:31:59,318 --> 00:32:00,103
Understand?

510
00:32:00,857 --> 00:32:02,166
I’m counting on you.

511
00:32:08,200 --> 00:32:09,155
Tor Prakai.

512
00:32:09,687 --> 00:32:11,734
is the new Likay hero of our troupe.

513
00:32:11,734 --> 00:32:15,066
I’m going to make you
a nationally famous Likay hero.

514
00:32:15,066 --> 00:32:17,066
Yay!

515
00:32:19,133 --> 00:32:20,720
All the things you wanted me to do—

516
00:32:21,695 --> 00:32:23,677
did you ever ask if I wanted them too?

517
00:32:25,300 --> 00:32:27,166
Or have you only ever cared about yourself?

518
00:32:28,300 --> 00:32:29,456
Why would you think that?

519
00:32:31,566 --> 00:32:33,366
Did your boyfriend teach you to think like this?

520
00:32:58,333 --> 00:32:59,800
There’s so much food today.

521
00:33:02,533 --> 00:33:04,000
Who’s grabbing what first?

522
00:33:22,133 --> 00:33:22,933
Eat up.

523
00:33:26,466 --> 00:33:26,966
Ploy.

524
00:33:26,966 --> 00:33:27,933
Thank you.

525
00:33:38,000 --> 00:33:39,300
It’s okay, I’ll serve myself.

526
00:33:40,466 --> 00:33:41,266
Thank you.

527
00:33:56,366 --> 00:33:57,351
Have some soup.

528
00:33:58,503 --> 00:33:59,447
You’re only eating fried food.

529
00:34:00,000 --> 00:34:00,998
Your throat’s gonna dry out.

530
00:34:07,933 --> 00:34:09,500
You haven’t even apologized to each other yet,

531
00:34:09,866 --> 00:34:11,400
and you’re already taking care of each other like this.

532
00:34:12,566 --> 00:34:14,866
If this isn’t making up,

533
00:34:15,266 --> 00:34:16,459
then I don’t know what is.

534
00:34:16,459 --> 00:34:16,966
True.

535
00:34:18,933 --> 00:34:19,733
Cute, huh?

536
00:34:29,466 --> 00:34:29,966
Here.

537
00:34:30,000 --> 00:34:30,896
I’ll help.

538
00:34:30,896 --> 00:34:32,170
No need.

539
00:34:38,400 --> 00:34:40,800
Now this is the real “Baan Phid Prakai.”

540
00:34:51,940 --> 00:34:53,100
Pleng!

541
00:34:53,100 --> 00:34:55,975
You could just take one piece
instead of the whole plate.

542
00:35:55,600 --> 00:35:57,166
I wanted to talk about today.

543
00:35:58,425 --> 00:35:59,266
Oops.

544
00:35:59,266 --> 00:36:00,533
This room is so pretty.

545
00:36:01,200 --> 00:36:02,866
Can I go in and take some pictures?

546
00:36:10,900 --> 00:36:12,066
This angle should work.

547
00:36:13,800 --> 00:36:15,090
I wanted to talk about—

548
00:36:15,090 --> 00:36:15,590
Ow!

549
00:36:15,590 --> 00:36:16,090
Oh!

550
00:36:19,000 --> 00:36:19,800
Uh…

551
00:36:20,133 --> 00:36:21,166
Someone’s in here?

552
00:36:21,900 --> 00:36:22,700
Uh…

553
00:36:22,866 --> 00:36:25,266
Where’s the bathroom again? I forgot the way.

554
00:36:27,300 --> 00:36:28,466
O-Over there.

555
00:36:29,700 --> 00:36:30,500
Okay.

556
00:36:37,733 --> 00:36:39,400
Why can’t he just say it already?

557
00:36:40,800 --> 00:36:41,447
Maybe

558
00:36:41,447 --> 00:36:43,200
the heavens don’t want this settled yet.

559
00:36:46,866 --> 00:36:47,666
Oh.

560
00:36:47,933 --> 00:36:48,966
So you’re here.

561
00:36:49,466 --> 00:36:51,300
I was just about to hang the laundry.

562
00:36:52,166 --> 00:36:52,966
Uh…

563
00:36:53,066 --> 00:36:54,700
Where’s the drying rack?

564
00:36:59,666 --> 00:37:00,466
(Nine) Over there.
(Tor Prakai) Right there.

565
00:37:01,333 --> 00:37:04,333
Ah, okay. Thank you.

566
00:37:23,366 --> 00:37:24,700
So, have you two cleared things up yet?

567
00:37:25,166 --> 00:37:26,766
You’ve been walking circles around the house.

568
00:37:27,700 --> 00:37:29,933
Hm, not yet.

569
00:37:32,000 --> 00:37:33,866
People keep interrupting us.

570
00:37:35,566 --> 00:37:37,366
Maybe the time just hasn’t come yet.

571
00:37:38,500 --> 00:37:40,000
Then… tonight,

572
00:37:40,000 --> 00:37:41,366
let’s talk it out again.

573
00:37:43,000 --> 00:37:44,300
No interruptions allowed.

574
00:37:46,533 --> 00:37:47,533
If someone interrupts again,

575
00:37:47,933 --> 00:37:49,133
we’re locking the house door.

576
00:37:51,000 --> 00:37:52,266
Don’t forget protection.

577
00:37:53,733 --> 00:37:54,566
P'Phet.

578
00:37:56,666 --> 00:37:58,710
No, I mean while driving,

579
00:37:59,065 --> 00:38:00,489
be careful.

580
00:38:01,166 --> 00:38:01,966
Oh.

581
00:38:03,600 --> 00:38:04,400
I see.

582
00:38:05,766 --> 00:38:06,566
What were you thinking?

583
00:38:08,066 --> 00:38:08,862
Alright then.

584
00:38:09,261 --> 00:38:11,932
I should pack up and head back.

585
00:38:26,766 --> 00:38:27,572
Lynchee.

586
00:38:27,838 --> 00:38:28,625
Let’s go.

587
00:38:28,625 --> 00:38:29,399
Come on.

588
00:38:30,466 --> 00:38:31,266
Bye-bye.

589
00:38:31,333 --> 00:38:32,133
Hurry up.

590
00:38:38,266 --> 00:38:39,653
(Phet Thae) Check your stuff carefully.
(Ploy Ying) It’s a long drive.

591
00:38:40,000 --> 00:38:41,000
It’s not nearby.

592
00:38:41,200 --> 00:38:42,533
P'Phet’s driving, right?

593
00:38:43,200 --> 00:38:44,175
Of course I am.

594
00:38:44,175 --> 00:38:44,724
Whoa.

595
00:38:44,724 --> 00:38:46,733
Good thing it’s you. If P'Ploy drove,
we’d better call a Grab.

596
00:38:46,733 --> 00:38:47,499
And what’s that supposed to mean?

597
00:38:47,666 --> 00:38:48,800
What’s wrong with my driving?

598
00:38:49,066 --> 00:38:50,334
Definitely better than yours.

599
00:38:50,334 --> 00:38:50,834
Exactly.

600
00:38:54,966 --> 00:38:56,094
Thank you so much.

601
00:38:56,094 --> 00:38:57,338
For taking care of my younger brother.

602
00:38:57,737 --> 00:39:00,732
And I’m sorry
all of us misunderstood you.

603
00:39:00,732 --> 00:39:02,094
No, it’s really okay.

604
00:39:02,094 --> 00:39:03,258
I completely understand.

605
00:39:03,879 --> 00:39:06,946
Seeing everyone talking again
is more than enough for me.

606
00:39:11,133 --> 00:39:11,933
Let’s go home.

607
00:39:14,600 --> 00:39:15,981
I wanna go home already.

608
00:39:15,981 --> 00:39:16,481
Okay.

609
00:39:18,900 --> 00:39:20,100
Then I’ll head back first.

610
00:39:20,333 --> 00:39:21,266
P'Phet.

611
00:39:21,866 --> 00:39:23,133
Don’t forget protection.

612
00:39:25,542 --> 00:39:27,066
(Tor Prakai) You—
(Nine) Oops.

613
00:39:27,066 --> 00:39:30,800
He means drive carefully.
Safe driving.

614
00:39:31,001 --> 00:39:32,200
Oh.

615
00:39:33,166 --> 00:39:33,966
You scared me.

616
00:39:34,866 --> 00:39:35,666
Sigh…

617
00:39:35,800 --> 00:39:37,269
Alright then, I’m heading back.

618
00:39:37,934 --> 00:39:39,588
I’ll drive.

619
00:39:39,588 --> 00:39:40,466
Okay, go on.

620
00:39:41,466 --> 00:39:42,266
P'Phet.

621
00:39:45,200 --> 00:39:46,300
Travel safely.

622
00:39:47,333 --> 00:39:49,133
P'Ploy, take care of him for me.

623
00:39:51,266 --> 00:39:52,205
Lynchee.

624
00:39:52,781 --> 00:39:54,377
Take care of Pleng too.

625
00:39:56,800 --> 00:39:58,611
The two of us will get going first.

626
00:39:58,966 --> 00:40:00,379
We have an online meeting with the studio.

627
00:40:01,266 --> 00:40:02,622
An online meeting?

628
00:40:02,622 --> 00:40:05,775
Late at night like this?

629
00:40:06,300 --> 00:40:08,900
You sure it’s a work meeting?

630
00:40:09,966 --> 00:40:10,997
That’s enough, you two.

631
00:40:11,263 --> 00:40:13,010
You’re gonna make Guy blush again.

632
00:40:13,733 --> 00:40:15,466
(Phet Thae) Alright, let’s go home.
(Ploy Ying) Let’s head home.

633
00:40:15,900 --> 00:40:16,600
Goodbye.

634
00:40:16,600 --> 00:40:17,533
Thanks for coming.

635
00:40:17,700 --> 00:40:18,256
Goodbye.

636
00:40:18,256 --> 00:40:19,200
Thanks for coming.

637
00:40:19,582 --> 00:40:20,166
See you.

638
00:40:20,166 --> 00:40:21,366
(Tor Prakai) Travel safely.
(Ploy Ying) Bye.

639
00:40:22,533 --> 00:40:24,514
(Tor Prakai) Bye-bye.
(Pleng Chai) Bye, see you.

640
00:40:38,066 --> 00:40:39,000
But tonight,

641
00:40:40,133 --> 00:40:41,900
do you really only want to talk about work?

642
00:40:43,566 --> 00:40:45,366
We should talk about work first.

643
00:40:46,500 --> 00:40:48,400
Then later—

644
00:40:50,866 --> 00:40:53,301
Nine, I’m flying back tomorrow.

645
00:40:53,523 --> 00:40:54,156
Don’t stay up too late.

646
00:40:54,954 --> 00:40:56,146
You have to take me to the airport.

647
00:40:56,866 --> 00:40:59,499
I know already, stop repeating yourself.

648
00:41:00,000 --> 00:41:00,653
Go on.

649
00:41:00,963 --> 00:41:02,711
(Nine) Go to sleep already.
(Ten) Okay, see you.

650
00:41:18,971 --> 00:41:20,217
♪ When I finally ♪

651
00:41:31,400 --> 00:41:32,312
Oh, P'Phet.

652
00:41:32,933 --> 00:41:34,022
You’re still awake?

653
00:41:35,166 --> 00:41:36,057
Or is it because

654
00:41:36,057 --> 00:41:38,666
you can’t stop thinking about
“Spark of Love Shining Through the Heart”?

655
00:41:38,666 --> 00:41:39,800
So you can’t sleep?

656
00:41:41,800 --> 00:41:42,733
I am thinking about it.

657
00:41:44,266 --> 00:41:46,100
But not just the Likay script.

658
00:41:46,366 --> 00:41:48,600
I’m thinking about the troupe’s future too.

659
00:41:56,733 --> 00:41:58,766
We’ve been through so much already, Ploy.

660
00:42:00,333 --> 00:42:03,177
I think it’s time for us to start something new.

661
00:42:03,576 --> 00:42:06,200
Something that truly speaks for people today.

662
00:42:08,666 --> 00:42:12,100
And something that speaks for our hearts too, right?

663
00:42:14,166 --> 00:42:14,935
Right.

664
00:42:15,334 --> 00:42:16,738
Including Guy too.

665
00:42:18,463 --> 00:42:21,865
It’s time for our family
to tell the same story again.

666
00:42:21,865 --> 00:42:23,124
Once more.

667
00:42:23,612 --> 00:42:25,529
Not on separate stages like before.

668
00:42:30,533 --> 00:42:31,434
That’s good.

669
00:42:33,384 --> 00:42:35,215
No matter how many new stories we begin,

670
00:42:35,658 --> 00:42:39,531
there’s one thing every script must have.

671
00:42:40,905 --> 00:42:42,332
The heart of Petchprakai.

672
00:42:46,013 --> 00:42:48,280
The next Likay story won’t be about returning to the past.

673
00:42:49,566 --> 00:42:51,800
It’ll be about building our future for real.

674
00:43:13,466 --> 00:43:14,266
Action.

675
00:43:25,266 --> 00:43:27,166
I don’t want to act anymore.

676
00:43:29,100 --> 00:43:30,533
If the person standing before me

677
00:43:33,533 --> 00:43:34,466
isn’t you.

678
00:43:44,400 --> 00:43:45,811
Then stop acting.

679
00:43:48,338 --> 00:43:49,700
Just stay in reality

680
00:43:51,606 --> 00:43:53,167
with me instead.

681
00:44:20,566 --> 00:44:21,543
So cute.

682
00:44:21,543 --> 00:44:22,523
That was so emotional.

683
00:44:23,986 --> 00:44:25,427
Alright, clear the frame.

684
00:44:25,604 --> 00:44:27,068
Change the scene, move the set.

685
00:44:27,423 --> 00:44:28,222
Thank you.

686
00:44:28,222 --> 00:44:29,199
(Tor Prakai) Thank you.
(Director) Great job.

687
00:44:48,600 --> 00:44:50,400
If you talk in that tone,

688
00:44:51,866 --> 00:44:54,066
you’ll definitely melt him.

689
00:44:56,466 --> 00:44:58,000
Then help me.

690
00:44:59,133 --> 00:45:00,733
Let’s melt together.

691
00:45:14,333 --> 00:45:16,300
Less sweet, just like usual.

692
00:45:18,500 --> 00:45:20,133
You really remember everything.

693
00:45:20,566 --> 00:45:22,733
How could I forget my boyfriend’s order?

694
00:45:36,877 --> 00:45:37,822
Hey.

695
00:45:37,866 --> 00:45:39,200
If you collapse,

696
00:45:39,800 --> 00:45:42,100
I’ll definitely end up carrying you out of here.

697
00:45:44,100 --> 00:45:45,466
Then I’ll stand properly.

698
00:45:46,866 --> 00:45:48,366
So I won’t be a burden to you.

699
00:45:54,533 --> 00:45:55,333
Hm?

700
00:45:56,366 --> 00:45:57,166
Refreshing.

701
00:45:57,666 --> 00:45:59,100
Come on, let’s get back to work.

702
00:46:17,533 --> 00:46:19,000
Every day’s exhausting, huh?

703
00:46:21,466 --> 00:46:22,266
Yeah.

704
00:46:26,366 --> 00:46:27,866
But when someone’s beside you,

705
00:46:30,533 --> 00:46:32,700
it always becomes the best day for me.

706
00:47:00,766 --> 00:47:02,733
Just a few more scenes until filming wraps.

707
00:47:03,333 --> 00:47:04,466
I don’t want it to end.

708
00:47:05,100 --> 00:47:05,900
Mm.

709
00:47:07,100 --> 00:47:10,333
But why does the atmosphere
feel strangely quiet today?

710
00:47:11,266 --> 00:47:14,366
Did you hear?
The investors aren’t funding the project anymore.

711
00:47:14,900 --> 00:47:17,271
Keep it down. They haven’t announced it yet.

712
00:47:17,271 --> 00:47:19,900
Don’t let management hear you
or we’re all screwed.

713
00:47:20,000 --> 00:47:23,630
But I saw Khun Phop and the investors
having an online meeting.

714
00:47:24,694 --> 00:47:25,933
The whole room went silent.

715
00:47:27,066 --> 00:47:29,000
An online meeting with the investors.

716
00:47:40,559 --> 00:47:42,825
♪ Bringing back memories ♪

717
00:47:43,612 --> 00:47:47,191
♪ Of my younger brother ♪

718
00:47:48,540 --> 00:47:50,230
♪ In my heart ♪

719
00:47:50,558 --> 00:47:54,952
♪ I long to see him ♪

720
00:47:56,590 --> 00:48:00,540
♪ Now I have come ♪

721
00:48:01,933 --> 00:48:03,175
♪ Sitting here ♪

722
00:48:04,416 --> 00:48:08,774
♪ Because I wished to see ♪

723
00:48:08,982 --> 00:48:10,982
♪ My dear younger brother ♪

724
00:48:12,235 --> 00:48:14,590
♪ I want to tell you ♪

725
00:48:15,024 --> 00:48:17,689
♪ That I understand ♪

726
00:48:18,548 --> 00:48:19,794
♪ The dreams ♪

727
00:48:20,521 --> 00:48:22,743
♪ Of my younger brother ♪

728
00:48:23,362 --> 00:48:25,362
♪ My dear one ♪

729
00:48:32,200 --> 00:48:33,765
The reason I wrote all this

730
00:48:35,715 --> 00:48:36,799
is because

731
00:48:38,166 --> 00:48:39,666
I wanted Guy to see it.

732
00:48:41,700 --> 00:48:43,500
That I finally understand him now.

733
00:49:05,100 --> 00:49:06,566
Will they keep filming?

734
00:49:10,100 --> 00:49:11,566
Or will it really end here?

735
00:49:13,533 --> 00:49:16,766
Did you hear? The investors
aren’t funding the project anymore.

736
00:49:17,166 --> 00:49:22,366
Khun Phop and the investors had an online meeting.
The whole room looked stressed out.

737
00:49:32,400 --> 00:49:33,200
P'Phet.

738
00:49:34,533 --> 00:49:36,666
If Guy’s dream disappears again,

739
00:49:40,500 --> 00:49:41,766
what would you say?

740
00:49:55,566 --> 00:49:56,207
Guy.

741
00:49:57,492 --> 00:49:59,472
I don’t know why, but suddenly,

742
00:49:59,472 --> 00:50:01,188
I miss you this much.

743
00:50:05,700 --> 00:50:07,400
Let’s hope it’s not a bad omen.

744
00:50:20,000 --> 00:50:22,929
♪ If you fear it may be too late ♪

745
00:50:23,641 --> 00:50:25,641
♪ Already ♪

746
00:50:27,366 --> 00:50:32,375
♪ Then you must make your heart brave ♪

747
00:50:34,466 --> 00:50:36,599
♪ If you let it slip away ♪

748
00:50:37,568 --> 00:50:40,499
♪ Do not waste the time ♪

749
00:50:41,404 --> 00:50:42,650
♪ Everything ♪

750
00:50:43,333 --> 00:50:45,333
♪ Has value ♪

751
00:50:45,723 --> 00:50:47,989
♪ Worth cherishing ♪

752
00:50:50,623 --> 00:50:51,813
♪ If ♪

753
00:50:53,143 --> 00:50:57,426
♪ You choose silence and hide your heart ♪

754
00:50:58,216 --> 00:51:00,000
♪ Then everything ♪

755
00:51:00,942 --> 00:51:03,230
♪ Will crumble ♪

756
00:51:04,651 --> 00:51:08,734
♪ Apart ♪

757
00:51:26,200 --> 00:51:27,282
Is the news true?

758
00:51:27,282 --> 00:51:27,782
Yes.

759
00:51:28,200 --> 00:51:29,733
They officially announced it already.

760
00:51:30,100 --> 00:51:31,166
What should we do?

761
00:51:31,400 --> 00:51:33,600
Pleng, call Guy right now.

762
00:51:34,500 --> 00:51:35,300
P'Phet.

763
00:51:36,266 --> 00:51:38,166
You really want me to go back to performing Likay?

764
00:51:38,333 --> 00:51:39,894
Nine and Guy are back.

765
00:51:39,894 --> 00:51:40,500
Hey!

766
00:51:40,866 --> 00:51:41,666
Hello.

767
00:51:41,733 --> 00:51:44,000
Hello.

768
00:51:48,800 --> 00:51:49,733
Ping Pong Chae.
